# ToolGenerator

Offline multi-agent tool-use conversation generator.

Internship assessment project.

## Installation

1. `git clone <repo>`
2. `cd toolgenerator`
3. Download ToolBench data from Google Drive and place at `data/toolenv/tools/`
4. `pip install -e .`
5. Run: `toolgenerator build --tools-path data/toolenv/tools`

## Run End-To-End

1. `toolgenerator build --tools-path data/toolenv/tools`
2. `toolgenerator generate --output artifacts/generated.jsonl --num 100 --seed 42`
3. `toolgenerator validate --input artifacts/generated.jsonl`
4. `toolgenerator metrics --input artifacts/generated.jsonl`

## Diversity Experiment

Run A, corpus memory disabled:
`toolgenerator generate --output artifacts/run_a.jsonl --num 100 --seed 42 --no-corpus-memory`

Run B, corpus memory enabled:
`toolgenerator generate --output artifacts/run_b.jsonl --num 100 --seed 42`

Compare the two runs:
`toolgenerator metrics --input artifacts/run_a.jsonl --compare artifacts/run_b.jsonl`

## Tests

Run the full test suite with:
`pytest tests/`
